The "1D" simply means: Our DP state can be stored in a single array.

Example: dp[i]

Only one variable (i) is changing.

You are climbing a staircase. It takes n steps to reach the top.Each time you can either climb 1 or 2 steps. In how many distinct ways\
can you climb to the top?

So if:

f(i) = number of ways to reach stair i

then:

f(i) = f(i-1) + f(i-2)

Why?

Because every path to stair i must end with either:

(i-1) -> i   (1-step jump)

or

(i-2) -> i   (2-step jump)

So all ways to reach i are:

ways to reach (i-1)
+
ways to reach (i-2)


class Solution {
public:
    int climbStairs(int n) {

        if(n <= 2)
            return n;

        int prev2 = 1; //dp[1]
        int prev1 = 2;  //dp[2]

        for(int i = 3; i <= n; i++) {
            int cur = prev1 + prev2;

//for the next starirs teh prev would chnage na 

            prev2 = prev1;
            prev1 = cur;
        }

        return prev1;
    }
};
